<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-501-847  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 501 847.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>The Wall Street Journal  Oct 16 1990 pB1(W) pB1(E) 21 col in.andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>MCI and Sprint pitch 800 service to households. (MCICommunications Corp., US Sprint Communications Corp.) (Marketing)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Carnevale, Mary Lu.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>There is a new service for residential telephone customers: 800numbers for households.andP;  MCI Communications Corp offers, startingOct 15, 1990, a 'Personal 800' service, which allows customers toset up an 800 number to receive long-distance calls at theirhomes.andP;  US Sprint Communications Corp introduced a similar serviceearlier in Oct 1990, and analysts believe ATandamp;T, too, will enterthis market.andP;  The service targets parents with children atcollege, people with large families scattered in various parts ofthe country and small businesses.andP;  Companies price servicesdifferently: Sprint bills customers $10 a month and applies normallong-distance charges to calls that a customer receives (a $50installation fee will be waived during the first three months);and MCI offers options that depend on services that a customerwants and times the services are used.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   MCI Communications Corp. (services)US Sprint Communications Co. (services).andO;Ticker:    MCIC.andO;Topic:     Telephone companiesMarketing.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>